This directory contains a language definition for the Zinc family of languages for
use with GtkSourceView, the syntax highlighting library used by a number of
GNOME applications, such as gedit and Anjuta.

The Zinc language definition file, zinc.lang, can be installed globally by copying
it to the directory:

   /usr/share/gtksourceview-2.0/language-specs

or locally, by copying it to the directory:

   ~/.local/share/gtksourceview-2.0/language-specs
